author: News Tribune
title: Cross Country: Jeff City girls and boys finish second at Camdenton
text:
Share 
CAMDENTON — The Jefferson City girls and boys cross country teams came in second at the Camdenton Invitational on Saturday. 
Both Lee’s Summit West teams finished first, with the boys scoring 36 and the girls 42. The Jays finished their race with a score of 41, while the Lady Jays totaled 72. 
In the boys race, Jackson Schwartz led the Jays by finishing in third place with a time of 16:14. 
Also for Jefferson City, Saxon Teubner came in seventh (16:28), Cole Biesemeyer was eighth (16:36), Courtney Fitch was 10th (16:39), Landon Dunlap was 13th (16:48), Thomas Nield was 15th (16:56) and Brendan Bena was 23rd (17:23). 
In the girls race, Jayelee Payton led Jefferson City by finishing third in 19:35. 
Also for the Lady Jays, Ryan Esterline was 10th (20:04), Katie Ruth was 15th (20:13), Brianne Bechtel was 19th (20:27), Brenna Duncan was 25th (20:48), Syleste Martinez was 26th (20:49) and Alivia Bopp was 27th (20:49). 
The Jefferson City junior varsity teams both finished first. Josh Sabala won the race for the Jays in 17:43, while Kenzie Gourley of the Lady Jays was victorious in 21:09. ﻿
